declare_parcel_as_script_with_stdin <<'/---'
Handle *extended glob expressions* (i.e., pure-`zsh` string matching patterns
roughly analogous to regular expressions).
/---

# ....................{ TESTERS                            }....................
#FIXME: Globally rename "_characters" to "_chars", much as we did so earlier by
#renaming "_arguments" to "_args".
declare_function_with_stdin <<'/---'
[status: boolean] is_string_contains_characters_glob(string text)

Report success if the passed string contains at least one glob-reserved
character, notably including most ASCII punctuation (e.g., `[`, `<`, `(`, `|`).
/---
function is_string_contains_characters_glob() {
    die_unless_arg 'Expected one string.'
    is "${1}" == *['[]<>()|+*?#~^']* si
}

# --------------------( WASTELANDS                         )--------------------
